<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><entry xmlns:functx="http://www.functx.com" xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="entry_kælæn" xml:lang="os"><form type="lemma"><orth>kælæn</orth></form><sense><sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>колдовство</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>sorcery</q></cit></sense><sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>чары</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>magic</q></cit></sense><sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>чародейство</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>witchcraft</q></cit></sense></sense><re><re><form type="lemma"><orth>kælæn kænyn</orth></form><sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>наводить чары</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>to cast a spell</q></cit></sense></re><re><form type="lemma"><orth>kælæn-gænæg</orth></form><sense><sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>колдун</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>sorcerer</q></cit></sense><sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>чародей</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>wizard</q></cit></sense><sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>колдунья</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>sorceress</q></cit></sense></sense></re></re><cit type="exampleGroup"><cit type="example"><quote>Satana wydi arvy xīn æmæ zæxxy kælæn</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>Шатана (героиня нартовского эпоса) обладала колдовством неба и чарами земли</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>Shatana (a heroine of the Nart epics) possessed the witchcraft of heaven and spells of the earth</q></cit></cit><cit type="example"><quote>æmbæxsgæ ūt, kælængænæg yssæwy</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>спрячьтесь, идет колдун</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>hide, a sorcerer is coming</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Брит."/><biblScope>86</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example"><quote>wærtæ wæ kælængænægæn jæ kælændon</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>вон место колдовства вашего колдуна</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>The place of your sorcerer’s witchcraft is over there</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Брит."/><biblScope>82</biblScope></bibl></cit></cit><cit type="exampleGroup"><cit type="example"><quote>Satana wydi arvy xīn æmæ zæxxy kælæn</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>Шатана (героиня нартовского эпоса) обладала колдовством неба и чарами земли</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>Shatana (a heroine of the Nart epics) possessed the witchcraft of heaven and spells of the earth</q></cit></cit><cit type="example"><quote>æmbæxsgæ ūt, kælængænæg yssæwy</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>спрячьтесь, идет колдун</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>hide, a sorcerer is coming</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Брит."/><biblScope>86</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example"><quote>wærtæ wæ kælængænægæn jæ kælændon</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>вон место колдовства вашего колдуна</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>The place of your sorcerer’s witchcraft is over there</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Брит."/><biblScope>82</biblScope></bibl></cit></cit><etym xml:lang="ru">Вероятно, восходит к %i*karyana-%i от %ikar-%i ‘(чаро)действовать’. О связи понятий ‘действовать’ и ‘чародействовать’ см. <bibl><ref target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>528</biblScope></bibl>: гр. %iέργον%i ‘дело’ и %iόργια%i ‘культовое действие’, иран. %ivarz-%i ‘делать’ и русск. %iворожить%i, иран. %ikar-%i ‘действовать’ и лит. %ikeras%i ‘колдовство’, русск. %iчары%i. — К осетинскому примыкает <mentioned xml:lang=""><lang/><w>kälæ</w><gloss><q>чародейство</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang=""><w/><gloss><q>ворожба</q></gloss></mentioned>, , ср. %ikälæ xežæ sæg%i ‘знахарь’. В %bякутском%b отмечено <mentioned xml:lang="sah"><lang/><w>kälänī</w><gloss><q>дух-спутник, покровитель и помощник шамана</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl/>%bСб. Музея антрополог, и этногр. V 186%b). Быть может, <mentioned xml:lang="sah"><lang/><w>kälänī</w></mentioned>идет из <mentioned xml:lang="xsc"><lang/><w>*kalana</w></mentioned> (ос. %ikælæn%i), как %iшаман%i из др.инд. %išramana-%i.</etym><etym xml:lang="en">Probably it traces back to %i*karyana-%i from %ikar-%i ‘to do (magic)’. See <bibl><ref target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>528</biblScope></bibl> about the relation between ‘to do’ and ‘to do magic’: Greek %iέργον%i ‘work’ and %iόργια%i ‘cult action’, Iranian %ivarz-%i ‘to do’ and Russian %iворожить%i ‘tell fortunes’, Iranian %ikar-%i ‘to act’ and Lithuanina %ikeras%i ‘sorcery’, Russian %iчары%i ‘charms’. — <mentioned xml:lang=""><lang/><w>kälæ</w><gloss><q>witchcraft</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang=""><w/><gloss><q>fortune-telling</q></gloss></mentioned>, , is close to Ossetic, cf. %ikälæ xežæ sæg%i ‘witch-doctor’. In %bYakut%b there is the word <mentioned xml:lang="sah"><lang/><w>kälänī</w><gloss><q>a companion spirit, the protector and the helper of a shaman</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><biblScope>Collection of the Museum of Anthropology and Ethnography V 186</biblScope></bibl>). Maybe <mentioned xml:lang="sah"><lang/><w>kälänī</w></mentioned> is from <mentioned xml:lang="xsc"><lang/><w>*kalana</w></mentioned> (Ossetic %ikælæn%i), as Russian %iшаман%i 'shaman' is from Old Indic %išramana-%i.</etym></entry>